03/11/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A group of anarchists fought with police in the northern city of Thessaloniki early Sunday (November 2nd), injuring eight police officers. The clashes erupted after the group of youths attacked a bank and about 30 cars with firebombs near the campus of the University of Thessaloniki. Police say they arrested nine of the attackers. (ANA-MPA, In.news, Kathimerini, SKAI, AP, Gazeta.ru - 02/11/08) 
